modules.description: Generates points on a sphere's surface using a mathematical algorithm based on the generalized spiral method. Operates on integers representing the number of points and returns arrays of 3D coordinate tuples. Useful for simulations requiring evenly distributed sample points in spherical geometry.

Generates lists of 2D polar coordinates and 3D Cartesian coordinates based on a given integer parameter. The module works with lists of float tuples representing points in spherical and Cartesian spaces. It is used to create structured coordinate sets for simulations or geometric visualizations.
